-- Factbox: Makeup of jury in Rajaratnam trial
-- 
-- Wed Mar 9, 2011 5:40pm EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2011/03/09/us-galleon-rajaratnam-jurors-idUSTRE7287LI20110309

 

 (Reuters) - A panel of seven women and five men are serving on the jury in the criminal insider trading trial of hedge fund founder Raj Rajaratnam in New York. 

 The 12 jurors, plus six alternates, were selected on Wednesday from a pool of about 150 people. They will hear evidence in the case over the next two months. The following is some information about the 12 jurors, based on what they said in court in response to questions from the judge: 1. A 49-year-old woman who works for the Metropolitan Transit Authority. 2. A woman who once volunteered in the Israeli defense force. 3. A woman who likes to watch TV shows including "True Blood" and "Grey's Anatomy." 4. A 49-year-old woman from Manhattan who works in food services for New York City's Board of Education. 5. A 61-year-old woman from Westchester County, New York who works as nurse. 6. A 53-year-old woman who lives in Westchester County and works for the New York City Board of Education. 7. A 68-year-old man who has lived in Manhattan for 10 years. 8. A 46-year-old woman from the Bronx who works in special education. 9. A 56-year-old man from the Bronx who works in graphics at Apple Inc. 10. A 48-year-old man who lives in the Bronx and works for New York City's child services department. 11. A 53-year-old woman from Westchester County who works at Verizon Communications Inc. 12. A 55-year-old man who works as an MTA customer service representative. (Reporting by Basil Katz)